Virtuix Holdings  $1.50 million  Financing. Jan Goetgeluk  Submitted Aug 21  SEC Filing


08/24/2015  by OctaStaff 
			in Private Financing News 












Share with your friendsYour NameYour EmailRecipient EmailEnter a MessageI read this article and found it very interesting, thought it might be interesting for you. The article is called Virtuix Holdings  $1.50 million  Financing. Jan Goetgeluk  Submitted Aug 21  SEC Filing and is was published by Octafinance.com at http://www.octafinance.com/virtuix-holdings-1-50-million-financing-jan-goetgeluk-submitted-aug-21-sec-filing/173152/.CaptchaSubmit
Virtuix Holdings  Financing
Virtuix Holdings Inc., Corporation just  filed form D  announcing $1.50 million debt financing. This is a new filing. Virtuix Holdings  was able to  finance itself with $879,701 so far. That is 58.65% of the  fundraising offer. The total  private offering amount was $1.50 million.  The financing form was filed on 2015-08-21. The reason for the financing was: unspecified.  The fundraising still has about $620,299 more and is not closed yet. We have to wait more to see if the offering will be fully taken.
 Virtuix Holdings  is based in Texas. The  company’s business is Computers. The  SEC form was  signed by Jan Goetgeluk Chief Executive Officer.  The company was incorporated in 2014. The filler’s address is: 1826 Kramer Lane, Suite H, Austin, Tx, Texas, 78758.  Jan Goetgeluk is the related person in the form and it has address: 1826 Kramer Lane, Suite H, Austin, Tx, Texas, 78758. Link to Virtuix Holdings  Filing: 000120919115067413.
Analysis of Virtuix Holdings  Offering
On average,  companies in the Computers sector, sell 85.30% of the total offering  size. Virtuix Holdings  sold 58.65% of the offering.  The fundraising is still open. The average  fundraising size for companies in the Computers industry is $130,000. The total amount raised is 576.69% bigger than the average for companies in the Computers sector. The minimum investment for this  offering  was set at $10000. If you know more about the reasons for the  fundraising, please comment below.
What is Form D? What It Is Used For
Form D disclosures could be used to track and understand better your competitors. The information in Form D is usually highly confidential for ventures and startups and they don’t like revealing it. This is because it reveals amount raised or planned to be raised as well as reasons for the financing. This could help competitors. Entrepreneurs usually want to keep their financing a ‘secret’ so they can stay in stealth mode for longer.
Why Fundraising Reporting Is Good For Virtuix Holdings  Also
The Form D signed by Jan Goetgeluk might help Virtuix Holdings Inc.’s sector. First, it helps potential customers feel more safe to deal with a firm that is well financed. The odds are higher that it will stay in the business. Second, this could attract other investors such as venture-capital firms, funds and angels. Third, positive PR effects could even bring leasing firms and venture lenders.

